CD22


Description

B-cell receptor CD22 (CD22). Mediates B-cell B-cell interactions. May be involved in the localization of B-cells in lymphoid tissues. It seems to be involved in regulation of B-cell antigen receptor signaling.

NCT03638206 - Colorectal Cancer, Esophagus Cancer, Renal Carcinoma, Hepatoma, Lung Cancer, Mesothelioma, Ovarian Cancer, Pancreatic Cancer, Melanoma
